-- Nigeria's forex reserves rise 0.89 month-on-month to $38.14 billion 
-- 
-- Wed Apr 30, 2014 09:03AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, April 30 (Reuters) - Nigeria's foreign exchange reserves rose 0.89 percent month-on-month to $38.14 billion by April 28, from $37.80 billion by March 28, data from the central bank showed on Wednesday.

The forex reserves of Africa's biggest economy however dipped by 21.92 percent year-on-year as they stood at $48.85 billion a year earlier.